But Jack wants knowledge. He wants to know what happened to the world and why the United States was the only country to emerge from isolation. He has come across an ancient repository of information, something people once called the Library of Congress.

One Southern boy,  Jack, has been scavenging through the remains of the world. He has been finding many curious thin
Jack and his family are forced to live in a fallout shelter that they have converted into a home. Jack's father, who is the leader of the family, has taught Jack that the world outside is dangerous and that the only way to survive is to scavenge what they need from the ruins of the old world.

But Jack wants knowledge. He wants to know what happened to the world and why the United States was the only country to emerge from isolation. He has come across an ancient repository of information, something people once called the Library of Congress. Jack has learned how to use the library's computers to search for information, and he has been able to learn a great deal about the world.

But Jak wants knowledge. He wants to know what happened to the world and why the United States was the only country to emerge from isolation. He has come across an ancient repository of information, something people once called the Library of Congress. Jak has learned how to use the library's computers to search for information, and he has been able to learn a great deal about the world.

Internal powers begin to fight, and the world is destroyed in a nuclear war. Very few people survive.  Progress is set back generations.


One of the descendants of a survivor is a boy named Jak. Jak has been scavenging through the remains of the oworld. He has been finding many interesting things left from the war. 

Jak and his family are forced to live in a fallout shelter that they have converted into a home.  Jak's father, who is the leader of the family, has taught Jak that the world outside is dangerous and that the only way to survive is to scavenge what they need from the ruins of the old world.

But Jak wants knowledge. He wants to know what happened to the world and why the United States was the only country to emerge from isolation. He has come across an ancient repository of information, something people once called the Library of Congress. Jak has learned how to use the library's computers to search for information, and he has been able to learn a great deal about the world. 

Jak has been working on building his own computer. He has been able to salvage some of the parts from the old world, but he is missing a few key components. He is also working on a water purification system. His father has told him that water is the most important thing to have in the post-apocalyptic world.
